scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection includes employment-related files for the scientific staff of the Rockefeller Institute for Medical Research (later The Rockefeller University). The files appear to have originated as files on personnel kept by the Business Manager's Office.

Files typically include a copy of a formal grant application or an application for a staff appointment, letters of recommendation, correspondence with the head of the respective laboratory department, formal notices of appointments, renewal or resignation notices, and similar materials. For international applicants there is frequently correspondence with the Office of Immigration. Some files include clippings, obituaries, and photographs.

Dates given in the finding aid refer to the dates covered by the materials in the folder, not to the dates of appointment at the Rockefeller Institute. For information on the latter, the researcher may wish to consult "A History of the Rockefeller Institute, 1901-1953" by George W. Corner, published by the Rockefeller Institute Press, 1964.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The files are arranged in alphabetical order by last name.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Materials
relatedmaterial.p: For materials related to faculty, staff, and others associated with the Institute/University, the researcher may wish to consult FA259 Rockefeller University Campus Office Biographical Files. Some individuals may also have papers available. Consult Archivist for identification of pertinent materials and further assistance.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The collection contains material ranging from 1904 through the 1960s. Some files include clippings or obituary information published in the 1970s and 1980s.
